      "date": "2016-06-13 17:36:31.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1\n\n(3 comments)\n\nI think it should be made more generic with a shell variable that you can declare as your own wget tool.\n\nAlso why do you need lbuild, I wonder? For my local testing I only usemake, and if you need rpms, you could do make rpms, I guess.\n\nOr are you building release package with it like this all the time?",
