      "date": "2016-06-14 02:24:43.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n(1 comment)\n\nYeah, for local test, I use \"sh autogen.sh && ./configure $OPT && make && make rpms\" too. But we are trying to run tests on some virtual machines, which means the VMs needs to change kernel RPMs from time to time. And in this case, lbuild is useful. Current lbuild works perfectly in Tokyo, which has good network, but not in Shanghai unfortunately.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
